album.desc:
Happy New Year!

2018 is off to a good start. 

We celebrated New Year's Eve with Alva, Nicole, Ulysses and Ana in their new house up in the Berkeley hills with a good view of the fireworks.

New Year's Day, we did our annual Tennessee Valley hike.

images.title: Host
images.desc:
Come in! Come in! Happy end of 2017!

Hi Alva.
images.copyright: ©2018 Dean and Lucie Moses, all rights reserved

images.title: Hostess
images.desc:
Nicole cooked up a delicious feast... clams, chicken, roasted cauliflower and more. 

A tasty goodbye to 2017.
images.copyright: ©2018 Dean and Lucie Moses, all rights reserved

images.desc: The artwork on the wall is a portrait of Alva by Miriam.
images.copyright: ©2018 Dean and Lucie Moses, all rights reserved

images.title: Ulysses
images.desc:
Hi Ulysses!

Note the guitar in the background. At some point during the night, Alva strummed Auld Lang Syne (with punk-like flair) and we all sang along.

A note to our French readers: Auld Lang Syne is an old Scottish folk song. For some reason, it's the de rigueur song of New Year's Eve in the United States.
images.copyright: ©2018 Dean and Lucie Moses, all rights reserved

images.title: La Tigra
images.desc:
Milo grabbed the camera and asked us to give him our best La Tigra. 

Those of you who have seen the movie Zoolander will understand.

images.title: Four Legs
images.desc:
Wait... four legs in the air?!? Is something terribly amiss with Ana? 

Don't worry. It's Ana + her best friend Stella. Stella's parents were away partying somewhere else, while Stella partied with us.

images.title: Hike
images.desc:
The family tradition is to hike Tennessee Valley the day after Thanksgiving.

However, Higgsy was with us this Thanksgiving and dogs aren't allowed on that trail. 

Today we finally got to scratch our Tennessee Valley itch.
